Method Detail

fetch

public static void fetch(boolean forced,
                         java.lang.String tag)

Fetch an ad from the ad server. An ad will be not be fetched if there is no internet connection, an ad has already been fetched for the specified tag, or if forced is false.

Unless you set the flag HeyzapAds.DISABLE_AUTOMATIC_FETCH when starting Heyzap, you do not need to fetch before an ad is shown.

Parameters:
forced - whether to force a fetch in the case when an ad is already available.
tag - the tagged ad to fetch. The fetch will fail of the tag is turned off.
See Also:
HeyzapAds.OnStatusListener

display

public static void display(android.app.Activity activity,
                           java.lang.String tag)

Display an ad. If the ad has not been fetched, one will be fetched for the specified tag. Please be warned that unless the ad has been pre-fetched, there will be some delay between calling display and the ad showing on the screen.

If the tag has been turned off on the Heyzap dashboard, you will receive both a onFetchFailed and a onFailedToShow callback.

Parameters:
activity - The currently visible Activity.
tag - The tag used to fetch the ad.
See Also:
HeyzapAds.OnStatusListener#onShow(String)}, HeyzapAds.OnStatusListener#onFailedToShow(String)}, HeyzapAds.OnStatusListener#onFetchFailed(String)}

Display an ad. If the ad has not been fetched, one will be fetched. Please be warned that unless the ad has been pre-fetched, there will be some delay between calling display and the ad showing on the screen.

If the tag has been turned off on the Heyzap dashboard, you will receive both a HeyzapAds.OnStatusListener.onFailedToFetch(String) and a HeyzapAds.OnStatusListener.onFailedToShow(String) callback.
